All the rulers since CHIN Dynasty had adapted system of transporting rice by way of the ocean, but the most important ocean transportation system was that of YUAN dynasty. YUAN dynasty levied 1,211,000 SEOK per year, and some 1 million SEOK was collected in southern part of China.
It had been adapted the system to transport levied-rice by way of canal and inland waterway in the early of YUAN dynasty. But since it took long time and costed too much but it could transport rather little quantity, it could not satisfy the demand for the market. For overcoming these matters, YUAN dynasty took action to adapt new system to transport levied-rice by way of the ocean. There were scattered rocks, islets, and sands in northern passage. The vessel used for the northern passage was Chinese Junk, named Zhe-Yang ship. The characteristics of Zhe-Yang ship used for transporting levied-rice in YUAN dynasty is as follows; 
Firstly, it has the flat-bow and -stern and -bottom and it could sail in regardless of direction of wind and current. Secondly, bulkhead and longitudinal beam were used for strengthening the longitudinal and the transverse strength of the ship. Thirdly, since Zhe-Yang ship has little resistance against current because it has rather big L/B ratio and little draft, it could be maneuvered with ease in comparison of steep bottom vessel.

The purpose of this study is to analyze the components and to verify the relationship between employee satisfaction and customer orientation in shipping company. In order to achieve the purpose of this study, literature survey related to employee satisfaction and customer orientation was carried out and took a empirical analysis by the use of questionnaire method for employees in shipping company.
The final results and conclusions are as follows;
Customer orientation of shipping company is comprised of three levels like practical marketing concept, time/cost and technique/practical business. Moreover, employee satisfaction in shipping company has a positive effect on customer orientation in shipping company. Thus owners and managers of shipping companies should thorough grasp that the satisfaction and commitment of employees on their duties make an impact on their attitude which is to keep communication channel with customer and achieve effective relationship marketing to provide high quality service. On the basis of that, it should be considered and included company's strategic practice
